# Global Trade Insight: Impact on GDP

## 📊 Project Overview
A comprehensive data analytics capstone project analyzing the relationship between international trade openness and macroeconomic growth using World Bank World Development Indicators. This project measures trade intensity (exports + imports as % of GDP) against annual GDP growth across 200+ countries over six decades.

**Key Finding:** Global trade-GDP correlation is 0.08, indicating trade is a contributing but non-deterministic factor in economic growth. Institutional quality, human capital, and infrastructure are equally critical.

