## 📊 Derived Metrics & Calculations

### Trade Openness Index
```
Trade Openness (% of GDP) = Exports (% of GDP) + Imports (% of GDP)
```
**Interpretation:** Measures degree of participation in global trade relative to domestic economy.

### DAX Measures (Power BI)
```dax
Trade Openness % of GDP = 
  SUM('WDI'[Exports of goods and services(% of GDP)]) + 
  SUM('WDI'[Imports of goods and services(% of GDP)])
```

### Correlation Analysis
- **Method:** Pearson correlation coefficient
- **Variables:** Trade Openness % vs. Annual GDP Growth %
- **Result:** r = 0.08 (weak positive)

